  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: From Adam to Abraham'
      title: From Adam to Abraham
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]  Adam, Seth, Enosh; '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: '  Many names in these genealogies are spelled differently in other
          biblical books  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech,
        and Tiras. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath,[[COMMENT(0)]] and Togarmah. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Rodanim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put, and Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raamah, and Sabteca. The
        sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Cush fathered Nimrod. He was the first on earth to be a mighty man.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Egypt fathered Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Pathrusim, Casluhim (from whom the Philistines came), and Caphtorim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Canaan fathered Sidon his firstborn and Heth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram. And
        the sons of Aram:[[COMMENT(0)]] Uz, Hul, Gether, and Meshech. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Arpachshad fathered Shelah, and Shelah fathered Eber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "To Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg[[COMMENT(0)]]
        (for in his days the earth was divided), and his brother\u2019s name was
        Joktan. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:19 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Obal,[[COMMENT(0)]] Abimael, Sheba, '
      comments:
      - number: '1:22 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac (compare Genesis 10:28); Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Shem, Arpachshad, Shelah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Eber, Peleg, Reu; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Serug, Nahor, Terah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: From Abraham to Jacob'
      title: From Abraham to Jacob
      number: 27
      content: 'Abram, that is, Abraham.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Abraham: Isaac and Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'These are their genealogies: the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth,
        and Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The sons of Keturah, Abraham\u2019s concubine: she bore Zimran, Jokshan,
        Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. The sons of Jokshan: Sheba and Dedan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Midian: Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All
        these were the descendants of Keturah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Abraham fathered Isaac. The sons of Isaac: Esau and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of Esau: Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The sons of Eliphaz: Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, Kenaz, and of Timna,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Amalek. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:36 '
        content: 'Septuagint (compare Genesis 36:12); Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '  The sons of Seir: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer, and
        Dishan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "The sons of Lotan: Hori and Hemam;[[COMMENT(0)]] and Lotan\u2019s
        sister was Timna. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:39 '
        content: 'Septuagint (compare Genesis 36:22); Hebrew '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The sons of Shobal: Alvan,[[COMMENT(0)]] Manahath, Ebal, Shepho,
        and Onam. The sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:40 '
        content: 'Septuagint (compare Genesis 36:23); Hebrew Septuagint (compare
          Genesis 36:23); Hebrew '
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The son[[COMMENT(0)]] of Anah: Dishon. The sons of Dishon: Hemdan,
        Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:41 '
        content: 'Hebrew Septuagint (compare Genesis 36:26); Hebrew '
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan.[[COMMENT(0)]] The sons
        of Dishan: Uz and Aran.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:42 '
        content: 'Septuagint (compare Genesis 36:27); Hebrew '
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '  These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any
        king reigned over the people of Israel: Bela the son of Beor, the name of
        his city being Dinhabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his
        place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the
        country of Moab, reigned in his place, the name of his city being Avith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth on the Euphrates[[COMMENT(0)]]
        reigned in his place. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:48 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Shaul died, and Baal-hanan, the son of Achbor, reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Baal-hanan died, and Hadad reigned in his place, the name of his
        city being Pai; and his wife\u2019s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred,
        the daughter of Mezahab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'And Hadad died.The chiefs of Edom were: chiefs Timna, Alvah, Jetheth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: Magdiel, and Iram; these are the chiefs of Edom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Genealogy of David'
      title: A Genealogy of David
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the sons of Israel: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar,
        Zebulun, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The sons of Judah: Er, Onan and Shelah; these three Bath-shua the
        Canaanite bore to him. Now Er, Judah\u2019s firstborn, was evil in the sight
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and he put him to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'His daughter-in-law Tamar also bore him Perez and Zerah. Judah had
        five sons in all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sons of Perez: Hezron and Hamul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Zerah: Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Dara, five in
        all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The son[[COMMENT(0)]] of Carmi: Achan, the troubler of Israel, who
        broke faith in the matter of the devoted thing; '
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and Ethan\u2019s son was Azariah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Hezron that were born to him: Jerahmeel, Ram, and Chelubai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Ram fathered Amminadab, and Amminadab fathered Nahshon, prince of
        the sons of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Nahshon fathered Salmon,[[COMMENT(0)]] Salmon fathered Boaz, '
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        content: 'Septuagint (compare Ruth 4:21); Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Boaz fathered Obed, Obed fathered Jesse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jesse fathered Eliab his firstborn, Abinadab the second, Shimea the
        third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ozem the sixth, David the seventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And their sisters were Zeruiah and Abigail. The sons of Zeruiah:
        Abishai, Joab, and Asahel, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Abigail bore Amasa, and the father of Amasa was Jether the Ishmaelite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Caleb the son of Hezron fathered children by his wife Azubah, and
        by Jerioth; and these were her sons: Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When Azubah died, Caleb married Ephrath, who bore him Hur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Hur fathered Uri, and Uri fathered Bezalel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of
        Gilead, whom he married when he was sixty years old, and she bore him Segub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Segub fathered Jair, who had twenty-three cities in the land
        of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But Geshur and Aram took from them Havvoth-jair, Kenath, and its
        villages, sixty towns. All these were descendants of Machir, the father of
        Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'After the death of Hezron, Caleb went in to Ephrathah,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the wife of Hezron his father, and she bore him Ashhur, the father of Tekoa.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:24 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The sons of Jerahmeel, the firstborn of Hezron: Ram, his firstborn,
        Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Jerahmeel also had another wife, whose name was Atarah; she was the
        mother of Onam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Ram, the firstborn of Jerahmeel: Maaz, Jamin, and Eker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Onam: Shammai and Jada. The sons of Shammai: Nadab and
        Abishur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The name of Abishur\u2019s wife was Abihail, and she bore him Ahban
        and Molid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The sons of Nadab: Seled and Appaim; and Seled died childless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The son[[COMMENT(0)]] of Appaim: Ishi. The son of Ishi: Sheshan.
        The son of Sheshan: Ahlai. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:31 '
        content: Hebrew ; three times in this verse
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The sons of Jada, Shammai\u2019s brother: Jether and Jonathan; and
        Jether died childless. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Jonathan: Peleth and Zaza. These were the descendants
        of Jerahmeel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now Sheshan had no sons, only daughters, but Sheshan had an Egyptian
        slave whose name was Jarha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'So Sheshan gave his daughter in marriage to Jarha his slave, and
        she bore him Attai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Attai fathered Nathan, and Nathan fathered Zabad. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zabad fathered Ephlal, and Ephlal fathered Obed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Obed fathered Jehu, and Jehu fathered Azariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Azariah fathered Helez, and Helez fathered Eleasah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Eleasah fathered Sismai, and Sismai fathered Shallum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Shallum fathered Jekamiah, and Jekamiah fathered Elishama.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sons of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel: Mareshah[[COMMENT(0)]]
        his firstborn, who fathered Ziph. The son of Mareshah: Hebron.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:42 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The sons of Hebron: Korah, Tappuah, Rekem and Shema. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Shema fathered Raham, the father of Jorkeam; and Rekem fathered Shammai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The son of Shammai: Maon; and Maon fathered Beth-zur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Ephah also, Caleb\u2019s concubine, bore Haran, Moza, and Gazez;
        and Haran fathered Gazez. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The sons of Jahdai: Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah, and Shaaph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Maacah, Caleb\u2019s concubine, bore Sheber and Tirhanah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'She also bore Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of
        Machbenah and the father of Gibea; and the daughter of Caleb was Achsah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'These were the descendants of Caleb.The sons[[COMMENT(0)]] of Hur
        the firstborn of Ephrathah: Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim, '
      comments:
      - number: '2:50 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Salma, the father of Bethlehem, and Hareph the father of Beth-gader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim had other sons: Haroeh, half
        of the Menuhoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And the clans of Kiriath-jearim: the Ithrites, the Puthites, the
        Shumathites, and the Mishraites; from these came the Zorathites and the Eshtaolites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The sons of Salma: Bethlehem, the Netophathites, Atroth-beth-joab
        and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'The clans also of the scribes who lived at Jabez: the Tirathites,
        the Shimeathites and the Sucathites. These are the Kenites who came from
        Hammath, the father of the house of Rechab.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of David'
      title: Descendants of David
      number: 1
      content: '    These are the sons of David who were born to him in Hebron: the
        firstborn, Amnon, by Ahinoam the Jezreelite; the second, Daniel, by Abigail
        the Carmelite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'the third, Absalom, whose mother was Maacah, the daughter of Talmai,
        king of Geshur; the fourth, Adonijah, whose mother was Haggith; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the fifth, Shephatiah, by Abital; the sixth, Ithream, by his wife
        Eglah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'six were born to him in Hebron, where he reigned for seven years
        and six months. And he reigned thirty-three years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'These were born to him in Jerusalem: Shimea, Shobab, Nathan and Solomon,
        four by Bath-shua, the daughter of Ammiel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'then Ibhar, Elishama, Eliphelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "All these were David\u2019s sons, besides the sons of the concubines,
        and Tamar was their sister.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The son of Solomon was Rehoboam, Abijah his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat
        his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Amon his son, Josiah his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Josiah: Johanan the firstborn, the second Jehoiakim,
        the third Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The descendants of Jehoiakim: Jeconiah his son, Zedekiah his son; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and the sons of Jeconiah, the captive: Shealtiel his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Malchiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jekamiah, Hoshama and Nedabiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and the sons of Pedaiah: Zerubbabel and Shimei; and the sons of Zerubbabel:
        Meshullam and Hananiah, and Shelomith was their sister; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and Hashubah, Ohel, Berechiah, Hasadiah, and Jushab-hesed, five. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Hananiah: Pelatiah and Jeshaiah, his son[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Rephaiah, his son Arnan, his son Obadiah, his son Shecaniah. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:21 '
        content: Septuagint (compare Syriac, Vulgate); Hebrew ; four times in this
          verse
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The son[[COMMENT(0)]] of Shecaniah: Shemaiah. And the sons of Shemaiah:
        Hattush, Igal, Bariah, Neariah, and Shaphat, six. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:22 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Neariah: Elioenai, Hizkiah, and Azrikam, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Elioenai: Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan,
        Delaiah, and Anani, seven.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Judah'
      title: Descendants of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    The sons of Judah: Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur, and Shobal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Reaiah the son of Shobal fathered Jahath, and Jahath fathered Ahumai
        and Lahad. These were the clans of the Zorathites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'These were the sons[[COMMENT(0)]] of Etam: Jezreel, Ishma, and Idbash;
        and the name of their sister was Hazzelelponi, '
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        content: 'Septuagint (compare Vulgate); Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Penuel fathered Gedor, and Ezer fathered Hushah. These were the
        sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, the father of Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ashhur, the father of Tekoa, had two wives, Helah and Naarah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni, and Haahashtari. These were
        the sons of Naarah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Helah: Zereth, Izhar, and Ethnan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Koz fathered Anub, Zobebah, and the clans of Aharhel, the son of
        Harum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jabez was more honorable than his brothers; and his mother called
        his name Jabez, saying, \u201CBecause I bore him in pain.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:9 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jabez called upon the God of Israel, saying, \u201COh that you would
        bless me and enlarge my border, and that your hand might be with me, and
        that you would keep me from harm[[COMMENT(0)]] so that it might not bring
        me pain!\u201D And God granted what he asked. "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Chelub, the brother of Shuhah, fathered Mehir, who fathered Eshton. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Eshton fathered Beth-rapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah, the father of Ir-nahash.
        These are the men of Recah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Kenaz: Othniel and Seraiah; and the sons of Othniel:
        Hathath and Meonothai.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Meonothai fathered Ophrah; and Seraiah fathered Joab, the father
        of Ge-harashim,[[COMMENT(0)]] so-called because they were craftsmen. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:14 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh: Iru, Elah, and Naam; and
        the son[[COMMENT(0)]] of Elah: Kenaz. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:15 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Jehallelel: Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Ezrah: Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon. These are the
        sons of Bithiah, the daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered married;[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and she conceived and bore Miriam, Shammai, and Ishbah, the father of Eshtemoa. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:17 '
        content: 'The clause is transposed from verse 18Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And his Judahite wife bore Jered the father of Gedor, Heber the father
        of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of the wife of Hodiah, the sister of Naham, were the fathers
        of Keilah the Garmite and Eshtemoa the Maacathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Shimon: Amnon, Rinnah, Ben-hanan, and Tilon. The sons
        of Ishi: Zoheth and Ben-zoheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Shelah the son of Judah: Er the father of Lecah, Laadah
        the father of Mareshah, and the clans of the house of linen workers at Beth-ashbea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and Jokim, and the men of Cozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who ruled
        in Moab and returned to Lehem[[COMMENT(0)]] (now the records are ancient). '
      comments:
      - number: '4:22 '
        content: 'Vulgate (compare Septuagint); Hebrew Or '
    - name: '23: Descendants of Simeon'
      title: Descendants of Simeon
      number: 23
      content: "These were the potters who were inhabitants of Netaim and Gederah.
        They lived there in the king\u2019s service.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  The sons of Simeon: Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, Shaul; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Shallum was his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The sons of Mishma: Hammuel his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers did not
        have many children, nor did all their clan multiply like the men of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They lived in Beersheba, Moladah, Hazar-shual, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Bilhah, Ezem, Tolad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susim, Beth-biri, and Shaaraim. These were
        their cities until David reigned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And their villages were Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Tochen, and Ashan, five
        cities, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'along with all their villages that were around these cities as far
        as Baal. These were their settlements, and they kept a genealogical record.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Meshobab, Jamlech, Joshah the son of Amaziah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Joel, Jehu the son of Joshibiah, son of Seraiah, son of Asiel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, Benaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Ziza the son of Shiphi, son of Allon, son of Jedaiah, son of Shimri,
        son of Shemaiah\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "these mentioned by name were princes in their clans, and their fathers\u2019
        houses increased greatly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'They journeyed to the entrance of Gedor, to the east side of the
        valley, to seek pasture for their flocks, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'where they found rich, good pasture, and the land was very broad,
        quiet, and peaceful, for the former inhabitants there belonged to Ham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'These, registered by name, came in the days of Hezekiah, king of
        Judah, and destroyed their tents and the Meunites who were found there, and
        marked them for destruction to this day, and settled in their place, because
        there was pasture there for their flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And some of them, five hundred men of the Simeonites, went to Mount
        Seir, having as their leaders Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the
        sons of Ishi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: And they defeated the remnant of the Amalekites who had escaped, and
        they have lived there to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Reuben'
      title: Descendants of Reuben
      number: 1
      content: "  The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel (for he was the firstborn,
        but because he defiled his father\u2019s couch, his birthright was given
        to the sons of Joseph the son of Israel, so that he could not be enrolled
        as the oldest son; "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'though Judah became strong among his brothers and a chief came from
        him, yet the birthright belonged to Joseph), '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the sons of Reuben, the firstborn of Israel: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron,
        and Carmi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Joel: Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Beerah his son, whom Tiglath-pileser[[COMMENT(0)]] king of Assyria
        carried away into exile; he was a chief of the Reubenites. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:6 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 26
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And his kinsmen by their clans, when the genealogy of their generations
        was recorded: the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and Bela the son of Azaz, son of Shema, son of Joel, who lived in
        Aroer, as far as Nebo and Baal-meon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He also lived to the east as far as the entrance of the desert this
        side of the Euphrates, because their livestock had multiplied in the land
        of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Descendants of Gad'
      title: Descendants of Gad
      number: 10
      content: 'And in the days of Saul they waged war against the Hagrites, who
        fell into their hand. And they lived in their tents throughout all the region
        east of Gilead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Gad lived over against them in the land of Bashan as
        far as Salecah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Joel the chief, Shapham the second, Janai, and Shaphat in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And their kinsmen according to their fathers\u2019 houses: Michael,
        Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jacan, Zia and Eber, seven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These were the sons of Abihail the son of Huri, son of Jaroah, son
        of Gilead, son of Michael, son of Jeshishai, son of Jahdo, son of Buz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Ahi the son of Abdiel, son of Guni, was chief in their fathers\u2019
        houses, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and they lived in Gilead, in Bashan and in its towns, and in all
        the pasturelands of Sharon to their limits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All of these were recorded in genealogies in the days of Jotham king
        of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh had valiant
        men who carried shield and sword, and drew the bow, expert in war, 44,760,
        able to go to war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They waged war against the Hagrites, Jetur, Naphish, and Nodab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when they prevailed[[COMMENT(0)]] over them, the Hagrites and
        all who were with them were given into their hands, for they cried out to
        God in the battle, and he granted their urgent plea because they trusted
        in him. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They carried off their livestock: 50,000 of their camels, 250,000
        sheep, 2,000 donkeys, and 100,000 men alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Half-Tribe of Manasseh'
      title: The Half-Tribe of Manasseh
      number: 22
      content: 'For many fell, because the war was of God. And they lived in their
        place until the exile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The members of the half-tribe of Manasseh lived in the land. They
        were very numerous from Bashan to Baal-hermon, Senir, and Mount Hermon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "These were the heads of their fathers\u2019 houses: Epher,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Ishi, Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty warriors, famous
        men, heads of their fathers\u2019 houses. "
      comments:
      - number: '5:24 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But they broke faith with the God of their fathers, and whored after
        the gods of the peoples of the land, whom God had destroyed before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: So the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria,
        the spirit of Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, and he took them into exile,
        namely, the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, and
        brought them to Halah, Habor, Hara, and the river Gozan, to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Levi'
      title: Descendants of Levi
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]  The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: '  Ch 5:27 in Hebrew    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The children of Amram: Aaron, Moses, and Miriam. The sons of Aaron:
        Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Eleazar fathered Phinehas, Phinehas fathered Abishua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Abishua fathered Bukki, Bukki fathered Uzzi, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Uzzi fathered Zerahiah, Zerahiah fathered Meraioth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Meraioth fathered Amariah, Amariah fathered Ahitub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ahitub fathered Zadok, Zadok fathered Ahimaaz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ahimaaz fathered Azariah, Azariah fathered Johanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and Johanan fathered Azariah (it was he who served as priest in the
        house that Solomon built in Jerusalem). '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Azariah fathered Amariah, Amariah fathered Ahitub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Ahitub fathered Zadok, Zadok fathered Shallum, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Shallum fathered Hilkiah, Hilkiah fathered Azariah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Azariah fathered Seraiah, Seraiah fathered Jehozadak; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and Jehozadak went into exile when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent Judah and Jerusalem into exile by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]] The sons of Levi: Gershom, Kohath, and Merari. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:16 '
        content: '  Ch 6:1 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And these are the names of the sons of Gershom: Libni and Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron and Uzziel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. These are the clans of the Levites
        according to their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Of Gershom: Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, Jeatherai his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Kohath: Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Elkanah his son, Ebiasaph his son, Assir his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, and Shaul his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The sons of Elkanah: Amasai and Ahimoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Elkanah his son, Zophai his son, Nahath his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, Elkanah his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The sons of Samuel: Joel[[COMMENT(0)]] his firstborn, the second
        Abijah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:28 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac (compare verse 33 and 1 Samuel 8:2); Hebrew
          lacks Hebrew '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzzah his
        son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, and Asaiah his son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'These are the men whom David put in charge of the service of song
        in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  after the ark rested there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They ministered with song before the tabernacle of the tent of meeting
        until Solomon built the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in Jerusalem,
        and they performed their service according to their order. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'These are the men who served and their sons. Of the sons of the Kohathites:
        Heman the singer the son of Joel, son of Samuel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'son of Elkanah, son of Jeroham, son of Eliel, son of Toah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'son of Zuph, son of Elkanah, son of Mahath, son of Amasai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'son of Elkanah, son of Joel, son of Azariah, son of Zephaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'son of Tahath, son of Assir, son of Ebiasaph, son of Korah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'son of Izhar, son of Kohath, son of Levi, son of Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and his brother Asaph, who stood on his right hand, namely, Asaph
        the son of Berechiah, son of Shimea, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'son of Michael, son of Baaseiah, son of Malchijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'son of Ethni, son of Zerah, son of Adaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'son of Ethan, son of Zimmah, son of Shimei, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'son of Jahath, son of Gershom, son of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'On the left hand were their brothers, the sons of Merari: Ethan the
        son of Kishi, son of Abdi, son of Malluch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'son of Hashabiah, son of Amaziah, son of Hilkiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'son of Amzi, son of Bani, son of Shemer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'son of Mahli, son of Mushi, son of Merari, son of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And their brothers the Levites were appointed for all the service
        of the tabernacle of the house of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'But Aaron and his sons made offerings on the altar of burnt offering
        and on the altar of incense for all the work of the Most Holy Place, and
        to make atonement for Israel, according to all that Moses the servant of
        God had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'These are the sons of Aaron: Eleazar his son, Phinehas his son, Abishua
        his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Bukki his son, Uzzi his son, Zerahiah his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Meraioth his son, Amariah his son, Ahitub his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Zadok his son, Ahimaaz his son.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'These are their dwelling places according to their settlements within
        their borders: to the sons of Aaron of the clans of Kohathites, for theirs
        was the first lot, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'to them they gave Hebron in the land of Judah and its surrounding
        pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'but the fields of the city and its villages they gave to Caleb the
        son of Jephunneh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'To the sons of Aaron they gave the cities of refuge: Hebron, Libnah
        with its pasturelands, Jattir, Eshtemoa with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Hilen with its pasturelands, Debir with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Ashan with its pasturelands, and Beth-shemesh with its pasturelands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'and from the tribe of Benjamin, Gibeon,[[COMMENT(0)]] Geba with its
        pasturelands, Alemeth with its pasturelands, and Anathoth with its pasturelands.
        All their cities throughout their clans were thirteen.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:60 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac (compare Joshua 21:17); Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: '  To the rest of the Kohathites were given by lot out of the clan
        of the tribe, out of the half-tribe, the half of Manasseh, ten cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'To the Gershomites according to their clans were allotted thirteen
        cities out of the tribes of Issachar, Asher, Naphtali and Manasseh in Bashan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'To the Merarites according to their clans were allotted twelve cities
        out of the tribes of Reuben, Gad, and Zebulun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'So the people of Israel gave the Levites the cities with their pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'They gave by lot out of the tribes of Judah, Simeon, and Benjamin
        these cities that are mentioned by name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: '  And some of the clans of the sons of Kohath had cities of their
        territory out of the tribe of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'They were given the cities of refuge: Shechem with its pasturelands
        in the hill country of Ephraim, Gezer with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: 'Jokmeam with its pasturelands, Beth-horon with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: 'Aijalon with its pasturelands, Gath-rimmon with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: 'and out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Aner with its pasturelands,
        and Bileam with its pasturelands, for the rest of the clans of the Kohathites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: '  To the Gershomites were given out of the clan of the half-tribe
        of Manasseh: Golan in Bashan with its pasturelands and Ashtaroth with its
        pasturelands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: 'and out of the tribe of Issachar: Kedesh with its pasturelands, Daberath
        with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: 'Ramoth with its pasturelands, and Anem with its pasturelands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '74: '
      title: 
      number: 74
      content: 'out of the tribe of Asher: Mashal with its pasturelands, Abdon with
        its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '75: '
      title: 
      number: 75
      content: 'Hukok with its pasturelands, and Rehob with its pasturelands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '76: '
      title: 
      number: 76
      content: 'and out of the tribe of Naphtali: Kedesh in Galilee with its pasturelands,
        Hammon with its pasturelands, and Kiriathaim with its pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '77: '
      title: 
      number: 77
      content: 'To the rest of the Merarites were allotted out of the tribe of Zebulun:
        Rimmono with its pasturelands, Tabor with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '78: '
      title: 
      number: 78
      content: 'and beyond the Jordan at Jericho, on the east side of the Jordan,
        out of the tribe of Reuben: Bezer in the wilderness with its pasturelands,
        Jahzah with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '79: '
      title: 
      number: 79
      content: 'Kedemoth with its pasturelands, and Mephaath with its pasturelands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '80: '
      title: 
      number: 80
      content: 'and out of the tribe of Gad: Ramoth in Gilead with its pasturelands,
        Mahanaim with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '81: '
      title: 
      number: 81
      content: Heshbon with its pasturelands, and Jazer with its pasturelands.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Issachar'
      title: Descendants of Issachar
      number: 1
      content: '  The sons[[COMMENT(0)]] of Issachar: Tola, Puah, Jashub, and Shimron,
        four. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:1 '
        content: 'Syriac (compare Vulgate); Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The sons of Tola: Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Ibsam, and Shemuel,
        heads of their fathers\u2019 houses, namely of Tola, mighty warriors of their
        generations, their number in the days of David being 22,600. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The son[[COMMENT(0)]] of Uzzi: Izrahiah. And the sons of Izrahiah:
        Michael, Obadiah, Joel, and Isshiah, all five of them were chief men. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:3 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verses 10, 12, 17
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And along with them, by their generations, according to their fathers\u2019
        houses, were units of the army for war, 36,000, for they had many wives and
        sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Descendants of Benjamin'
      title: Descendants of Benjamin
      number: 5
      content: 'Their kinsmen belonging to all the clans of Issachar were in all
        87,000 mighty warriors, enrolled by genealogy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The sons of Benjamin: Bela, Becher, and Jediael, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The sons of Bela: Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth, and Iri, five, heads
        of fathers\u2019 houses, mighty warriors. And their enrollment by genealogies
        was 22,034. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Becher: Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jeremoth,
        Abijah, Anathoth, and Alemeth. All these were the sons of Becher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And their enrollment by genealogies, according to their generations,
        as heads of their fathers\u2019 houses, mighty warriors, was 20,200. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The son of Jediael: Bilhan. And the sons of Bilhan: Jeush, Benjamin,
        Ehud, Chenaanah, Zethan, Tarshish, and Ahishahar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "All these were the sons of Jediael according to the heads of their
        fathers\u2019 houses, mighty warriors, 17,200, able to go to war. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Descendants of Naphtali'
      title: Descendants of Naphtali
      number: 12
      content: 'And Shuppim and Huppim were the sons of Ir, Hushim the son of Aher.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Descendants of Manasseh'
      title: Descendants of Manasseh
      number: 13
      content: '  The sons of Naphtali: Jahziel, Guni, Jezer and Shallum, the descendants
        of Bilhah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  The sons of Manasseh: Asriel, whom his Aramean concubine bore;
        she bore Machir the father of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Machir took a wife for Huppim and for Shuppim. The name of his
        sister was Maacah. And the name of the second was Zelophehad, and Zelophehad
        had daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Maacah the wife of Machir bore a son, and she called his name
        Peresh; and the name of his brother was Sheresh; and his sons were Ulam and
        Rakem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The son of Ulam: Bedan. These were the sons of Gilead the son of
        Machir, son of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And his sister Hammolecheth bore Ishhod, Abiezer, and Mahlah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Descendants of Ephraim'
      title: Descendants of Ephraim
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Shemida were Ahian, Shechem, Likhi, and Aniam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Ephraim: Shuthelah, and Bered his son, Tahath his son,
        Eleadah his son, Tahath his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, and Ezer and Elead, whom the men
        of Gath who were born in the land killed, because they came down to raid
        their livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Ephraim their father mourned many days, and his brothers came
        to comfort him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And Ephraim went in to his wife, and she conceived and bore a son.
        And he called his name Beriah, because disaster had befallen his house.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:23 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'His daughter was Sheerah, who built both Lower and Upper Beth-horon,
        and Uzzen-sheerah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Rephah was his son, Resheph his son, Telah his son, Tahan his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ladan his son, Ammihud his son, Elishama his son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Nun[[COMMENT(0)]] his son, Joshua his son. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:27 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Their possessions and settlements were Bethel and its towns, and
        to the east Naaran, and to the west Gezer and its towns, Shechem and its
        towns, and Ayyah and its towns; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Descendants of Asher'
      title: Descendants of Asher
      number: 29
      content: 'also in possession of the Manassites, Beth-shean and its towns, Taanach
        and its towns, Megiddo and its towns, Dor and its towns. In these lived the
        sons of Joseph the son of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, and their sister
        Serah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The sons of Beriah: Heber, and Malchiel, who fathered Birzaith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Heber fathered Japhlet, Shomer, Hotham, and their sister Shua. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The sons of Japhlet: Pasach, Bimhal, and Ashvath. These are the sons
        of Japhlet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The sons of Shemer his brother: Rohgah, Jehubbah, and Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of Helem his brother: Zophah, Imna, Shelesh, and Amal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The sons of Zophah: Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Ithran, and Beera. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The sons of Jether: Jephunneh, Pispa, and Ara. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The sons of Ulla: Arah, Hanniel, and Rizia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "All of these were men of Asher, heads of fathers\u2019 houses, approved,
        mighty warriors, chiefs of the princes. Their number enrolled by genealogies,
        for service in war, was 26,000 men."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Genealogy of Saul'
      title: A Genealogy of Saul
      number: 1
      content: '    Benjamin fathered Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second, Aharah
        the third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Nohah the fourth, and Rapha the fifth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Bela had sons: Addar, Gera, Abihud, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Gera, Shephuphan, and Huram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "These are the sons of Ehud (they were heads of fathers\u2019 houses
        of the inhabitants of Geba, and they were carried into exile to Manahath): "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Naaman,[[COMMENT(0)]] Ahijah, and Gera, that is, Heglam, who fathered
        Uzza and Ahihud. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Shaharaim fathered sons in the country of Moab after he had sent
        away Hushim and Baara his wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He fathered sons by Hodesh his wife: Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jeuz, Sachia, and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of fathers\u2019
        houses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He also fathered sons by Hushim: Abitub and Elpaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Elpaal: Eber, Misham, and Shemed, who built Ono and Lod
        with its towns, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and Beriah and Shema (they were heads of fathers\u2019 houses of
        the inhabitants of Aijalon, who caused the inhabitants of Gath to flee); "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and Ahio, Shashak, and Jeremoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Zebadiah, Arad, Eder, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Michael, Ishpah, and Joha were sons of Beriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Ishmerai, Izliah, and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Jakim, Zichri, Zabdi, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Ishpan, Eber, Eliel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Abdon, Zichri, Hanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hananiah, Elam, Anthothijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Iphdeiah, and Penuel were the sons of Shashak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Jaareshiah, Elijah, and Zichri were the sons of Jeroham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "These were the heads of fathers\u2019 houses, according to their
        generations, chief men. These lived in Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '    Jeiel[[COMMENT(0)]] the father of Gibeon lived in Gibeon, and
        the name of his wife was Maacah. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:29 '
        content: 'Compare 9:35; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'His firstborn son: Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Gedor, Ahio, Zecher, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'and Mikloth (he fathered Shimeah). Now these also lived opposite
        their kinsmen in Jerusalem, with their kinsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Ner was the father of Kish, Kish of Saul, Saul of Jonathan, Malchi-shua,
        Abinadab and Eshbaal; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'and the son of Jonathan was Merib-baal; and Merib-baal was the father
        of Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tarea, and Ahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Ahaz fathered Jehoaddah, and Jehoaddah fathered Alemeth, Azmaveth,
        and Zimri. Zimri fathered Moza. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Moza fathered Binea; Raphah was his son, Eleasah his son, Azel his
        son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Azel had six sons, and these are their names: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael,
        Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. All these were the sons of Azel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The sons of Eshek his brother: Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the second,
        and Eliphelet the third. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: The sons of Ulam were men who were mighty warriors, bowmen, having
        many sons and grandsons, 150. All these were Benjaminites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Genealogy of the Returned Exiles'
      title: A Genealogy of the Returned Exiles
      number: 1
      content: '  So all Israel was recorded in genealogies, and these are written
        in the Book of the Kings of Israel. And Judah was taken into exile in Babylon
        because of their breach of faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the first to dwell again in their possessions in their cities
        were Israel, the priests, the Levites, and the temple servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And some of the people of Judah, Benjamin, Ephraim, and Manasseh
        lived in Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Uthai the son of Ammihud, son of Omri, son of Imri, son of Bani,
        from the sons of Perez the son of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And of the Shilonites: Asaiah the firstborn, and his sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Of the sons of Zerah: Jeuel and their kinsmen, 690. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Of the Benjaminites: Sallu the son of Meshullam, son of Hodaviah,
        son of Hassenuah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ibneiah the son of Jeroham, Elah the son of Uzzi, son of Michri,
        and Meshullam the son of Shephatiah, son of Reuel, son of Ibnijah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and their kinsmen according to their generations, 956. All these
        were heads of fathers\u2019 houses according to their fathers\u2019 houses.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Of the priests: Jedaiah, Jehoiarib, Jachin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and Azariah the son of Hilkiah, son of Meshullam, son of Zadok, son
        of Meraioth, son of Ahitub, the chief officer of the house of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, son of Pashhur, son of Malchijah,
        and Maasai the son of Adiel, son of Jahzerah, son of Meshullam, son of Meshillemith,
        son of Immer; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "besides their kinsmen, heads of their fathers\u2019 houses, 1,760,
        mighty men for the work of the service of the house of God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam, son
        of Hashabiah, of the sons of Merari; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and Bakbakkar, Heresh, Galal and Mattaniah the son of Mica, son of
        Zichri, son of Asaph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, son of Galal, son of Jeduthun, and
        Berechiah the son of Asa, son of Elkanah, who lived in the villages of the
        Netophathites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The gatekeepers were Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, Ahiman, and their kinsmen
        (Shallum was the chief); '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "until then they were in the king\u2019s gate on the east side as
        the gatekeepers of the camps of the Levites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Shallum the son of Kore, son of Ebiasaph, son of Korah, and his kinsmen
        of his fathers\u2019 house, the Korahites, were in charge of the work of
        the service, keepers of the thresholds of the tent, as their fathers had
        been in charge of the camp of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, keepers of
        the entrance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Phinehas the son of Eleazar was the chief officer over them in
        time past; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Zechariah the son of Meshelemiah was gatekeeper at the entrance of
        the tent of meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'All these, who were chosen as gatekeepers at the thresholds, were
        212. They were enrolled by genealogies in their villages. David and Samuel
        the seer established them in their office of trust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So they and their sons were in charge of the gates of the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that is, the house of the tent, as guards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The gatekeepers were on the four sides, east, west, north, and south. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And their kinsmen who were in their villages were obligated to come
        in every seven days, in turn, to be with these, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'for the four chief gatekeepers, who were Levites, were entrusted
        to be over the chambers and the treasures of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And they lodged around the house of God, for on them lay the duty
        of watching, and they had charge of opening it every morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Some of them had charge of the utensils of service, for they were
        required to count them when they were brought in and taken out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Others of them were appointed over the furniture and over all the
        holy utensils, also over the fine flour, the wine, the oil, the incense,
        and the spices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Others, of the sons of the priests, prepared the mixing of the spices, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and Mattithiah, one of the Levites, the firstborn of Shallum the
        Korahite, was entrusted with making the flat cakes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Also some of their kinsmen of the Kohathites had charge of the showbread,
        to prepare it every Sabbath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Now these, the singers, the heads of fathers\u2019 houses of the
        Levites, were in the chambers of the temple free from other service, for
        they were on duty day and night. "
      comments: []
    - name: "34: Saul\u2019s Genealogy Repeated"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Genealogy Repeated"
      number: 34
      content: "These were heads of fathers\u2019 houses of the Levites, according
        to their generations, leaders. These lived in Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: '  In Gibeon lived the father of Gibeon, Jeiel, and the name of his
        wife was Maacah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and his firstborn son Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah, and Mikloth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and Mikloth was the father of Shimeam; and these also lived opposite
        their kinsmen in Jerusalem, with their kinsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Ner fathered Kish, Kish fathered Saul, Saul fathered Jonathan, Malchi-shua,
        Abinadab, and Eshbaal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And the son of Jonathan was Merib-baal, and Merib-baal fathered Micah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The sons of Micah: Pithon, Melech, Tahrea, and Ahaz.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:41 '
        content: 'Compare 8:35; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And Ahaz fathered Jarah, and Jarah fathered Alemeth, Azmaveth, and
        Zimri. And Zimri fathered Moza. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Moza fathered Binea, and Rephaiah was his son, Eleasah his son, Azel
        his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Azel had six sons and these are their names: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael,
        Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan; these were the sons of Azel.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Death of Saul and His Sons'
      title: The Death of Saul and His Sons
      number: 1
      content: '    Now the Philistines fought against Israel, and the men of Israel
        fled before the Philistines and fell slain on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Philistines overtook Saul and his sons, and the Philistines
        struck down Jonathan and Abinadab and Malchi-shua, the sons of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The battle pressed hard against Saul, and the archers found him,
        and he was wounded by the archers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Saul said to his armor-bearer, \u201CDraw your sword and thrust
        me through with it, lest these uncircumcised come and mistreat me.\u201D
        But his armor-bearer would not, for he feared greatly. Therefore Saul took
        his own sword and fell upon it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when his armor-bearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell upon
        his sword and died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Thus Saul died; he and his three sons and all his house died together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when all the men of Israel who were in the valley saw that the
        army[[COMMENT(0)]] had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned
        their cities and fled, and the Philistines came and lived in them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:7 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The next day, when the Philistines came to strip the slain, they
        found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they stripped him and took his head and his armor, and sent messengers
        throughout the land of the Philistines to carry the good news to their idols
        and to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they put his armor in the temple of their gods and fastened his
        head in the temple of Dagon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when all Jabesh-gilead heard all that the Philistines had done
        to Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'all the valiant men arose and took away the body of Saul and the
        bodies of his sons, and brought them to Jabesh. And they buried their bones
        under the oak in Jabesh and fasted seven days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Saul died for his breach of faith. He broke faith with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in that he did not keep the command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and
        also consulted a medium, seeking guidance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: He did not seek guidance from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Therefore
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> put him to death and turned the kingdom over
        to David the son of Jesse.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Anointed King'
      title: David Anointed King
      number: 1
      content: "    Then all Israel gathered together to David at Hebron and said,
        \u201CBehold, we are your bone and flesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In times past, even when Saul was king, it was you who led out and
        brought in Israel. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God said to you,
        \u2018You shall be shepherd of my people Israel, and you shall be prince
        over my people Israel.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: David Takes Jerusalem'
      title: David Takes Jerusalem
      number: 3
      content: 'So all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and David
        made a covenant with them at Hebron before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And they anointed David king over Israel, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by Samuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, that is, Jebus, where
        the Jebusites were, the inhabitants of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The inhabitants of Jebus said to David, \u201CYou will not come in
        here.\u201D Nevertheless, David took the stronghold of Zion, that is, the
        city of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "David said, \u201CWhoever strikes the Jebusites first shall be chief
        and commander.\u201D And Joab the son of Zeruiah went up first, so he became
        chief. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And David lived in the stronghold; therefore it was called the city
        of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he built the city all around from the Millo in complete circuit,
        and Joab repaired the rest of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      title: "David\u2019s Mighty Men"
      number: 9
      content: 'And David became greater and greater, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts was with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  Now these are the chiefs of David\u2019s mighty men, who gave him
        strong support in his kingdom, together with all Israel, to make him king,
        according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "This is an account of David\u2019s mighty men: Jashobeam, a Hachmonite,
        was chief of the three.[[COMMENT(0)]] He wielded his spear against 300 whom
        he killed at one time.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:11 '
        content: 'Compare 2 Samuel 23:8; Hebrew , or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And next to him among the three mighty men was Eleazar the son of
        Dodo, the Ahohite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He was with David at Pas-dammim when the Philistines were gathered
        there for battle. There was a plot of ground full of barley, and the men
        fled from the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But he took his[[COMMENT(0)]] stand in the midst of the plot and
        defended it and killed the Philistines. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        saved them by a great victory.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:14 '
        content: 'Compare 2 Samuel 23:12; Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Three of the thirty chief men went down to the rock to David at the
        cave of Adullam, when the army of Philistines was encamped in the Valley
        of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David was then in the stronghold, and the garrison of the Philistines
        was then at Bethlehem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And David said longingly, \u201COh that someone would give me water
        to drink from the well of Bethlehem that is by the gate!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines
        and drew water out of the well of Bethlehem that was by the gate and took
        it and brought it to David. But David would not drink it. He poured it out
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and said, \u201CFar be it from me before my God that I should do
        this. Shall I drink the lifeblood of these men? For at the risk of their
        lives they brought it.\u201D Therefore he would not drink it. These things
        did the three mighty men.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now Abishai, the brother of Joab, was chief of the thirty.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        And he wielded his spear against 300 men and killed them and won a name beside
        the three. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:20 '
        content: 'Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He was the most renowned[[COMMENT(0)]] of the thirty and became their
        commander, but he did not attain to the three.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:21 '
        content: 'Compare 2 Samuel 23:19; Hebrew Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was a valiant man[[COMMENT(0)]] of
        Kabzeel, a doer of great deeds. He struck down two heroes of Moab. He also
        went down and struck down a lion in a pit on a day when snow had fallen. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:22 '
        content: 'Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he struck down an Egyptian, a man of great stature, five cubits[[COMMENT(0)]]
        tall. The Egyptian had in his hand a spear like a weaver\u2019s beam, but
        Benaiah went down to him with a staff and snatched the spear out of the Egyptian\u2019s
        hand and killed him with his own spear. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:23 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada and won a name beside
        the three mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He was renowned among the thirty, but he did not attain to the three.
        And David set him over his bodyguard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The mighty men were Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of
        Dodo of Bethlehem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Shammoth of Harod,[[COMMENT(0)]] Helez the Pelonite, '
      comments:
      - number: '11:27 '
        content: 'Compare 2 Samuel 23:25; Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ira the son of Ikkesh of Tekoa, Abiezer of Anathoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Sibbecai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Maharai of Netophah, Heled the son of Baanah of Netophah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Ithai the son of Ribai of Gibeah of the people of Benjamin, Benaiah
        of Pirathon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Hurai of the brooks of Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Azmaveth of Baharum, Eliahba the Shaalbonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Hashem[[COMMENT(0)]] the Gizonite, Jonathan the son of Shagee the
        Hararite, '
      comments:
      - number: '11:34 '
        content: 'Compare Septuagint and 2 Samuel 23:32; Hebrew '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Ahiam the son of Sachar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Ur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Hepher the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Hezro of Carmel, Naarai the son of Ezbai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Joel the brother of Nathan, Mibhar the son of Hagri, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai of Beeroth, the armor-bearer of Joab
        the son of Zeruiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Uriah the Hittite, Zabad the son of Ahlai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Adina the son of Shiza the Reubenite, a leader of the Reubenites,
        and thirty with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Hanan the son of Maacah, and Joshaphat the Mithnite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Uzzia the Ashterathite, Shama and Jeiel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jediael the son of Shimri, and Joha his brother, the Tizite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Eliel the Mahavite, and Jeribai, and Joshaviah, the sons of Elnaam,
        and Ithmah the Moabite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: Eliel, and Obed, and Jaasiel the Mezobaite.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Mighty Men Join David'
      title: The Mighty Men Join David
      number: 1
      content: '    Now these are the men who came to David at Ziklag, while he could
        not move about freely because of Saul the son of Kish. And they were among
        the mighty men who helped him in war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "They were bowmen and could shoot arrows and sling stones with either
        the right or the left hand; they were Benjaminites, Saul\u2019s kinsmen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The chief was Ahiezer, then Joash, both sons of Shemaah of Gibeah;
        also Jeziel and Pelet, the sons of Azmaveth; Beracah, Jehu of Anathoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ishmaiah of Gibeon, a mighty man among the thirty and a leader over
        the thirty; Jeremiah,[[COMMENT(0)]] Jahaziel, Johanan, Jozabad of Gederah, '
      comments:
      - number: '12:4 '
        content: Hebrew verse 5
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Eluzai,[[COMMENT(0)]] Jerimoth, Bealiah, Shemariah, Shephatiah the
        Haruphite; '
      comments:
      - number: '12:5 '
        content: Hebrew verse 6
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Elkanah, Isshiah, Azarel, Joezer, and Jashobeam, the Korahites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Joelah and Zebadiah, the sons of Jeroham of Gedor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'From the Gadites there went over to David at the stronghold in the
        wilderness mighty and experienced warriors, expert with shield and spear,
        whose faces were like the faces of lions and who were swift as gazelles upon
        the mountains: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ezer the chief, Obadiah second, Eliab third, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Mishmannah fourth, Jeremiah fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Attai sixth, Eliel seventh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Johanan eighth, Elzabad ninth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jeremiah tenth, Machbannai eleventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These Gadites were officers of the army; the least was a match for
        a hundred men and the greatest for a thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'These are the men who crossed the Jordan in the first month, when
        it was overflowing all its banks, and put to flight all those in the valleys,
        to the east and to the west.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And some of the men of Benjamin and Judah came to the stronghold
        to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "David went out to meet them and said to them, \u201CIf you have come
        to me in friendship to help me, my heart will be joined to you; but if to
        betray me to my adversaries, although there is no wrong in my hands, then
        may the God of our fathers see and rebuke you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the Spirit clothed Amasai, chief of the thirty, and he said,\u201CWe
        are yours, O David,and with you, O son of Jesse!  Peace, peace to you,and
        peace to your helpers!For your God helps you.\u201DThen David received them
        and made them officers of his troops.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Some of the men of Manasseh deserted to David when he came with the
        Philistines for the battle against Saul. (Yet he did not help them, for the
        rulers of the Philistines took counsel and sent him away, saying, \u201CAt
        peril to our heads he will desert to his master Saul.\u201D) "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As he went to Ziklag, these men of Manasseh deserted to him: Adnah,
        Jozabad, Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu, and Zillethai, chiefs of thousands
        in Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They helped David against the band of raiders, for they were all
        mighty men of valor and were commanders in the army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For from day to day men came to David to help him, until there was
        a great army, like an army of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These are the numbers of the divisions of the armed troops who came
        to David in Hebron to turn the kingdom of Saul over to him, according to
        the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The men of Judah bearing shield and spear were 6,800 armed troops. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Of the Simeonites, mighty men of valor for war, 7,100. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Of the Levites 4,600. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The prince Jehoiada, of the house of Aaron, and with him 3,700. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Zadok, a young man mighty in valor, and twenty-two commanders from
        his own fathers\u2019 house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Of the Benjaminites, the kinsmen of Saul, 3,000, of whom the majority
        had to that point kept their allegiance to the house of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Of the Ephraimites 20,800, mighty men of valor, famous men in their
        fathers\u2019 houses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Of the half-tribe of Manasseh 18,000, who were expressly named to
        come and make David king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Of Issachar, men who had understanding of the times, to know what
        Israel ought to do, 200 chiefs, and all their kinsmen under their command. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Of Zebulun 50,000 seasoned troops, equipped for battle with all the
        weapons of war, to help David[[COMMENT(0)]] with singleness of purpose. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:33 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Of Naphtali 1,000 commanders with whom were 37,000 men armed with
        shield and spear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Of the Danites 28,600 men equipped for battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Of Asher 40,000 seasoned troops ready for battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Of the Reubenites and Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh from
        beyond the Jordan, 120,000 men armed with all the weapons of war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'All these, men of war, arrayed in battle order, came to Hebron with
        a whole heart to make David king over all Israel. Likewise, all the rest
        of Israel were of a single mind to make David king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And they were there with David for three days, eating and drinking,
        for their brothers had made preparation for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: And also their relatives, from as far as Issachar and Zebulun and
        Naphtali, came bringing food on donkeys and on camels and on mules and on
        oxen, abundant provisions of flour, cakes of figs, clusters of raisins, and
        wine and oil, oxen and sheep, for there was joy in Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Brought from Kiriath-Jearim'
      title: The Ark Brought from Kiriath-Jearim
      number: 1
      content: '  David consulted with the commanders of thousands and of hundreds,
        with every leader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David said to all the assembly of Israel, \u201CIf it seems good
        to you and from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, let us send abroad
        to our brothers who remain in all the lands of Israel, as well as to the
        priests and Levites in the cities that have pasturelands, that they may be
        gathered to us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then let us bring again the ark of our God to us, for we did not
        seek it[[COMMENT(0)]] in the days of Saul.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '13:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: Uzzah and the Ark'
      title: Uzzah and the Ark
      number: 4
      content: 'All the assembly agreed to do so, for the thing was right in the
        eyes of all the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  So David assembled all Israel from the Nile[[COMMENT(0)]] of Egypt
        to Lebo-hamath, to bring the ark of God from Kiriath-jearim. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And David and all Israel went up to Baalah, that is, to Kiriath-jearim
        that belongs to Judah, to bring up from there the ark of God, which is called
        by the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who sits enthroned above the
        cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they carried the ark of God on a new cart, from the house of
        Abinadab, and Uzzah and Ahio[[COMMENT(0)]] were driving the cart. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And David and all Israel were celebrating before God with all their
        might, with song and lyres and harps and tambourines and cymbals and trumpets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when they came to the threshing floor of Chidon, Uzzah put out
        his hand to take hold of the ark, for the oxen stumbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was kindled against
        Uzzah, and he struck him down because he put out his hand to the ark, and
        he died there before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And David was angry because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had broken
        out against Uzzah. And that place is called Perez-uzza[[COMMENT(0)]] to this
        day. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:11 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And David was afraid of God that day, and he said, \u201CHow can
        I bring the ark of God home to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So David did not take the ark home into the city of David, but took
        it aside to the house of Obed-edom the Gittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And the ark of God remained with the household of Obed-edom in his
        house three months. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> blessed the household
        of Obed-edom and all that he had.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Wives and Children"
      title: "David\u2019s Wives and Children"
      number: 1
      content: '    And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees,
        also masons and carpenters to build a house for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And David knew that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had established
        him as king over Israel, and that his kingdom was highly exalted for the
        sake of his people Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David took more wives in Jerusalem, and David fathered more sons
        and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These are the names of the children born to him in Jerusalem: Shammua,
        Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Philistines Defeated'
      title: Philistines Defeated
      number: 7
      content: 'Elishama, Beeliada and Eliphelet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over
        all Israel, all the Philistines went up to search for David. But David heard
        of it and went out against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the Philistines had come and made a raid in the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And David inquired of God, \u201CShall I go up against the Philistines?
        Will you give them into my hand?\u201D And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to him, \u201CGo up, and I will give them into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he went up to Baal-perazim, and David struck them down there.
        And David said, \u201CGod has broken through[[COMMENT(0)]] my enemies by
        my hand, like a bursting flood.\u201D Therefore the name of that place is
        called Baal-perazim. "
      comments:
      - number: '14:11 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they left their gods there, and David gave command, and they
        were burned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the Philistines yet again made a raid in the valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And when David again inquired of God, God said to him, \u201CYou
        shall not go up after them; go around and come against them opposite the
        balsam trees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the balsam
        trees, then go out to battle, for God has gone out before you to strike down
        the army of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And David did as God commanded him, and they struck down the Philistine
        army from Gibeon to Gezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And the fame of David went out into all lands, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        brought the fear of him upon all nations.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Brought to Jerusalem'
      title: The Ark Brought to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  David[[COMMENT(0)]] built houses for himself in the city of David.
        And he prepared a place for the ark of God and pitched a tent for it. '
      comments:
      - number: '15:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then David said that no one but the Levites may carry the ark of
        God, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had chosen them to carry the ark
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and to minister to him forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And David assembled all Israel at Jerusalem to bring up the ark of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  to its place, which he had prepared for
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And David gathered together the sons of Aaron and the Levites: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'of the sons of Kohath, Uriel the chief, with 120 of his brothers; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'of the sons of Merari, Asaiah the chief, with 220 of his brothers; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'of the sons of Gershom, Joel the chief, with 130 of his brothers; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'of the sons of Elizaphan, Shemaiah the chief, with 200 of his brothers; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'of the sons of Hebron, Eliel the chief, with 80 of his brothers; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'of the sons of Uzziel, Amminadab the chief, with 112 of his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then David summoned the priests Zadok and Abiathar, and the Levites
        Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel, and Amminadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and said to them, \u201CYou are the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses
        of the Levites. Consecrate yourselves, you and your brothers, so that you
        may bring up the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        to the place that I have prepared for it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Because you did not carry it the first time, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God broke out against us, because we did not seek him according to the
        rule.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the priests and the Levites consecrated themselves to bring up
        the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Levites carried the ark of God on their shoulders with the
        poles, as Moses had commanded according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David also commanded the chiefs of the Levites to appoint their brothers
        as the singers who should play loudly on musical instruments, on harps and
        lyres and cymbals, to raise sounds of joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the Levites appointed Heman the son of Joel; and of his brothers
        Asaph the son of Berechiah; and of the sons of Merari, their brothers, Ethan
        the son of Kushaiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and with them their brothers of the second order, Zechariah, Jaaziel,
        Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattithiah, Eliphelehu,
        and Mikneiah, and the gatekeepers Obed-edom and Jeiel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The singers, Heman, Asaph, and Ethan, were to sound bronze cymbals; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Zechariah, Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah, and
        Benaiah were to play harps according to Alamoth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'but Mattithiah, Eliphelehu, Mikneiah, Obed-edom, Jeiel, and Azaziah
        were to lead with lyres according to the Sheminith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Chenaniah, leader of the Levites in music, should direct the music,
        for he understood it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Berechiah and Elkanah were to be gatekeepers for the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Shebaniah, Joshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zechariah, Benaiah, and Eliezer,
        the priests, should blow the trumpets before the ark of God. Obed-edom and
        Jehiah were to be gatekeepers for the ark.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  So David and the elders of Israel and the commanders of thousands
        went to bring up the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        from the house of Obed-edom with rejoicing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And because God helped the Levites who were carrying the ark of the
        covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, they sacrificed seven bulls
        and seven rams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'David was clothed with a robe of fine linen, as also were all the
        Levites who were carrying the ark, and the singers and Chenaniah the leader
        of the music of the singers. And David wore a linen ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So all Israel brought up the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with shouting, to the sound of the horn, trumpets, and cymbals, and made
        loud music on harps and lyres.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And as the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to the city of David, Michal the daughter of Saul looked out of the
        window and saw King David dancing and celebrating, and she despised him in
        her heart.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Placed in a Tent'
      title: The Ark Placed in a Tent
      number: 1
      content: '  And they brought in the ark of God and set it inside the tent that
        David had pitched for it, and they offered burnt offerings and peace offerings
        before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when David had finished offering the burnt offerings and the
        peace offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and distributed to all Israel, both men and women, to each a loaf
        of bread, a portion of meat,[[COMMENT(0)]] and a cake of raisins.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:3 '
        content: Compare Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; the meaning of the Hebrew is
          uncertain
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then he appointed some of the Levites as ministers before the ark
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, to invoke, to thank, and to praise the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Asaph was the chief, and second to him were Zechariah, Jeiel, Shemiramoth,
        Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Benaiah, Obed-edom, and Jeiel, who were to play
        harps and lyres; Asaph was to sound the cymbals, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests were to blow trumpets regularly
        before the ark of the covenant of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: David\u2019s Song of Thanks"
      title: "David\u2019s Song of Thanks"
      number: 7
      content: 'Then on that day David first appointed that thanksgiving be sung
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> by Asaph and his brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Oh give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; call upon his
        name;  make known his deeds among the peoples!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Sing to him, sing praises to him;tell of all his wondrous works!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Glory in his holy name;let the hearts of those who seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        rejoice!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and his strength;seek his
        presence continually!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Remember the wondrous works that he has done,  his miracles and
        the judgments he uttered,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O offspring of Israel his servant,children of Jacob, his chosen ones!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God;  his judgments are
        in all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Remember his covenant forever,the word that he commanded, for a thousand
        generations,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the covenant that he made with Abraham,his sworn promise to Isaac,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'which he confirmed to Jacob as a statute,to Israel as an everlasting
        covenant,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "saying, \u201CTo you I will give the land of Canaan,as your portion
        for an inheritance.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When you were few in number,of little account, and sojourners in
        it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'wandering from nation to nation,from one kingdom to another people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'he allowed no one to oppress them;he rebuked kings on their account,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "saying, \u201CTouch not my anointed ones,do my prophets no harm!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all the earth!Tell of
        his salvation from day to day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Declare his glory among the nations,his marvelous works among all
        the peoples!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For great is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and greatly to be praised,and
        he is to be feared above all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For all the gods of the peoples are worthless idols,  but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        made the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Splendor and majesty are before him;strength and joy are in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ascribe to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, O families of the peoples, 
        ascribe to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> glory and strength!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Ascribe to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> the glory due his name;bring
        an offering and come before him!  Worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the splendor of holiness;[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:29 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'tremble before him, all the earth;yes, the world is established;
        it shall never be moved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  Let the heavens be glad, and let the earth rejoice,and let them
        say among the nations, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reigns!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '  Let the sea roar, and all that fills it;let the field exult, and
        everything in it!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then shall the trees of the forest sing for joybefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for he comes to judge the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Oh give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for he is good;for
        his steadfast love endures forever!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "  Say also:\u201CSave us, O God of our salvation,and gather and deliver
        us from among the nations,that we may give thanks to your holy nameand glory
        in your praise.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Worship Before the Ark'
      title: Worship Before the Ark
      number: 36
      content: "  Blessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,from
        everlasting to everlasting!\u201D  Then all the people said, \u201CAmen!\u201D
        and praised the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So David left Asaph and his brothers there before the ark of the
        covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to minister regularly before
        the ark as each day required, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and also Obed-edom and his[[COMMENT(0)]] sixty-eight brothers, while
        Obed-edom, the son of Jeduthun, and Hosah were to be gatekeepers. '
      comments:
      - number: '16:38 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And he left Zadok the priest and his brothers the priests before
        the tabernacle of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  in the high place that
        was at Gibeon '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'to offer burnt offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  on the
        altar of burnt offering regularly morning and evening, to do all that is
        written in the Law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he commanded Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'With them were Heman and Jeduthun and the rest of those chosen and
        expressly named to give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for his
        steadfast love endures forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Heman and Jeduthun had trumpets and cymbals for the music and instruments
        for sacred song. The sons of Jeduthun were appointed to the gate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '  Then all the people departed each to his house, and David went
        home to bless his household.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Covenant with David"
      title: "The \u2019s Covenant with David"
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    Now when David lived in his house,
        David said to Nathan the prophet, \u201CBehold, I dwell in a house of cedar,
        but the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is under a
        tent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Nathan said to David, \u201CDo all that is in your heart, for
        God is with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But that same night the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came
        to Nathan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGo and tell my servant David, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        It is not you who will build me a house to dwell in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For I have not lived in a house since the day I brought up Israel
        to this day, but I have gone from tent to tent and from dwelling to dwelling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In all places where I have moved with all Israel, did I speak a word
        with any of the judges of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd my people,
        saying, \u201CWhy have you not built me a house of cedar?\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now, therefore, thus shall you say to my servant David, \u2018Thus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, I took you from the pasture,
        from following the sheep, to be prince over my people Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and I have been with you wherever you have gone and have cut off
        all your enemies from before you. And I will make for you a name, like the
        name of the great ones of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I will appoint a place for my people Israel and will plant them,
        that they may dwell in their own place and be disturbed no more. And violent
        men shall waste them no more, as formerly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'from the time that I appointed judges over my people Israel. And
        I will subdue all your enemies. Moreover, I declare to you that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will build you a house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When your days are fulfilled to walk with your fathers, I will raise
        up your offspring after you, one of your own sons, and I will establish his
        kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He shall build a house for me, and I will establish his throne forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will be to him a father, and he shall be to me a son. I will not
        take my steadfast love from him, as I took it from him who was before you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "but I will confirm him in my house and in my kingdom forever, and
        his throne shall be established forever.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: David\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "David\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 15
      content: 'In accordance with all these words, and in accordance with all this
        vision, Nathan spoke to David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then King David went in and sat before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and said, \u201CWho am I, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God, and what is
        my house, that you have brought me thus far? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And this was a small thing in your eyes, O God. You have also spoken
        of your servant\u2019s house for a great while to come, and have shown me
        future generations,[[COMMENT(0)]] O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God! "
      comments:
      - number: '17:17 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And what more can David say to you for honoring your servant? For
        you know your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For your servant\u2019s sake, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and
        according to your own heart, you have done all this greatness, in making
        known all these great things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'There is none like you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and there
        is no God besides you, according to all that we have heard with our ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And who is like your people Israel, the one[[COMMENT(0)]] nation
        on earth whom God went to redeem to be his people, making for yourself a
        name for great and awesome things, in driving out nations before your people
        whom you redeemed from Egypt? '
      comments:
      - number: '17:21 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you made your people Israel to be your people forever, and you,
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, became their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, let the word that you have
        spoken concerning your servant and concerning his house be established forever,
        and do as you have spoken, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and your name will be established and magnified forever, saying,
        \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel, is Israel\u2019s
        God,\u2019 and the house of your servant David will be established before
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For you, my God, have revealed to your servant that you will build
        a house for him. Therefore your servant has found courage to pray before
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you are God, and you have
        promised this good thing to your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Now you have been pleased to bless the house of your servant, that
        it may continue forever before you, for it is you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who have blessed, and it is blessed forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Defeats His Enemies'
      title: David Defeats His Enemies
      number: 1
      content: '    After this David defeated the Philistines and subdued them, and
        he took Gath and its villages out of the hand of the Philistines.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he defeated Moab, and the Moabites became servants to David and
        brought tribute.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David also defeated Hadadezer king of Zobah-Hamath, as he went to
        set up his monument[[COMMENT(0)]] at the river Euphrates. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And David took from him 1,000 chariots, 7,000 horsemen, and 20,000
        foot soldiers. And David hamstrung all the chariot horses, but left enough
        for 100 chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah,
        David struck down 22,000 men of the Syrians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then David put garrisons[[COMMENT(0)]] in Syria of Damascus, and
        the Syrians became servants to David and brought tribute. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave victory to David wherever he went. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:6 '
        content: Septuagint, Vulgate, 2 Samuel 8:6 (compare Syriac); Hebrew lacks
          Hebrew <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  ; also verse
          13
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And David took the shields of gold that were carried by the servants
        of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And from Tibhath and from Cun, cities of Hadadezer, David took a
        large amount of bronze. With it Solomon made the bronze sea and the pillars
        and the vessels of bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Tou king of Hamath heard that David had defeated the whole army
        of Hadadezer, king of Zobah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'he sent his son Hadoram to King David, to ask about his health and
        to bless him because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him; for
        Hadadezer had often been at war with Tou. And he sent all sorts of articles
        of gold, of silver, and of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'These also King David dedicated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        together with the silver and gold that he had carried off from all the nations,
        from Edom, Moab, the Ammonites, the Philistines, and Amalek.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Abishai, the son of Zeruiah, killed 18,000 Edomites in the Valley
        of Salt. '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: David\u2019s Administration"
      title: "David\u2019s Administration"
      number: 13
      content: "Then he put garrisons in Edom, and all the Edomites became David\u2019s
        servants. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave victory to David wherever
        he went.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So David reigned over all Israel, and he administered justice and
        equity to all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army; and Jehoshaphat the
        son of Ahilud was recorder; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were
        priests; and Shavsha was secretary; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the
        Pelethites; and David\u2019s sons were the chief officials in the service
        of the king."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Ammonites Disgrace David\u2019s Men"
      title: "The Ammonites Disgrace David\u2019s Men"
      number: 1
      content: '    Now after this Nahash the king of the Ammonites died, and his
        son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David said, \u201CI will deal kindly with Hanun the son of Nahash,
        for his father dealt kindly with me.\u201D So David sent messengers to console
        him concerning his father. And David\u2019s servants came to the land of
        the Ammonites to Hanun to console him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the princes of the Ammonites said to Hanun, \u201CDo you think,
        because David has sent comforters to you, that he is honoring your father?
        Have not his servants come to you to search and to overthrow and to spy out
        the land?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Hanun took David\u2019s servants and shaved them and cut off their
        garments in the middle, at their hips, and sent them away; "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and they departed. When David was told concerning the men, he sent
        messengers to meet them, for the men were greatly ashamed. And the king said,
        \u201CRemain at Jericho until your beards have grown and then return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the Ammonites saw that they had become a stench to David, Hanun
        and the Ammonites sent 1,000 talents[[COMMENT(0)]] of silver to hire chariots
        and horsemen from Mesopotamia, from Aram-maacah, and from Zobah. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:6 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They hired 32,000 chariots and the king of Maacah with his army,
        who came and encamped before Medeba. And the Ammonites were mustered from
        their cities and came to battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When David heard of it, he sent Joab and all the army of the mighty
        men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Ammonites and Syrians Defeated'
      title: Ammonites and Syrians Defeated
      number: 9
      content: 'And the Ammonites came out and drew up in battle array at the entrance
        of the city, and the kings who had come were by themselves in the open country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When Joab saw that the battle was set against him both in front and
        in the rear, he chose some of the best men of Israel and arrayed them against
        the Syrians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The rest of his men he put in the charge of Abishai his brother,
        and they were arrayed against the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u201CIf the Syrians are too strong for me, then you
        shall help me, but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, then I will help
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Be strong, and let us use our strength for our people and for the
        cities of our God, and may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> do what seems
        good to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Joab and the people who were with him drew near before the Syrians
        for battle, and they fled before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when the Ammonites saw that the Syrians fled, they likewise fled
        before Abishai, Joab\u2019s brother, and entered the city. Then Joab came
        to Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But when the Syrians saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they
        sent messengers and brought out the Syrians who were beyond the Euphrates,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        with Shophach the commander of the army of Hadadezer at their head. '
      comments:
      - number: '19:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And when it was told to David, he gathered all Israel together and
        crossed the Jordan and came to them and drew up his forces against them.
        And when David set the battle in array against the Syrians, they fought with
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the Syrians fled before Israel, and David killed of the Syrians
        the men of 7,000 chariots and 40,000 foot soldiers, and put to death also
        Shophach the commander of their army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And when the servants of Hadadezer saw that they had been defeated
        by Israel, they made peace with David and became subject to him. So the Syrians
        were not willing to save the Ammonites anymore.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Capture of Rabbah'
      title: The Capture of Rabbah
      number: 1
      content: '    In the spring of the year, the time when kings go out to battle,
        Joab led out the army and ravaged the country of the Ammonites and came and
        besieged Rabbah. But David remained at Jerusalem. And Joab struck down Rabbah
        and overthrew it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And David took the crown of their king from his head. He found that
        it weighed a talent[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, and in it was a precious stone.
        And it was placed on David\u2019s head. And he brought out the spoil of the
        city, a very great amount. "
      comments:
      - number: '20:2 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '3: Philistine Giants Killed'
      title: Philistine Giants Killed
      number: 3
      content: 'And he brought out the people who were in it and set them to labor[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        with saws and iron picks and axes. And thus David did to all the cities of
        the Ammonites. Then David and all the people returned to Jerusalem.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:3 '
        content: 'Compare 2 Samuel 12:31; Hebrew Compare 2 Samuel 12:31; Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  And after this there arose war with the Philistines at Gezer. Then
        Sibbecai the Hushathite struck down Sippai, who was one of the descendants
        of the giants, and the Philistines were subdued. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And there was again war with the Philistines, and Elhanan the son
        of Jair struck down Lahmi the brother of Goliath the Gittite, the shaft of
        whose spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And there was again war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature,
        who had six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot, twenty-four in
        number, and he also was descended from the giants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when he taunted Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimea, David\u2019s
        brother, struck him down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: These were descended from the giants in Gath, and they fell by the
        hand of David and by the hand of his servants.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Census Brings Pestilence"
      title: "David\u2019s Census Brings Pestilence"
      number: 1
      content: '    Then Satan stood against Israel and incited David to number Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So David said to Joab and the commanders of the army, \u201CGo, number
        Israel, from Beersheba to Dan, and bring me a report, that I may know their
        number.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Joab said, \u201CMay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> add to his
        people a hundred times as many as they are! Are they not, my lord the king,
        all of them my lord\u2019s servants? Why then should my lord require this?
        Why should it be a cause of guilt for Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the king\u2019s word prevailed against Joab. So Joab departed
        and went throughout all Israel and came back to Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Joab gave the sum of the numbering of the people to David. In
        all Israel there were 1,100,000 men who drew the sword, and in Judah 470,000
        who drew the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he did not include Levi and Benjamin in the numbering, for the
        king\u2019s command was abhorrent to Joab.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But God was displeased with this thing, and he struck Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And David said to God, \u201CI have sinned greatly in that I have
        done this thing. But now, please take away the iniquity of your servant,
        for I have acted very foolishly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to Gad, David\u2019s seer,
        saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGo and say to David, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        Three things I offer you; choose one of them, that I may do it to you.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Gad came to David and said to him, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u2018Choose what you will: "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "either three years of famine, or three months of devastation by your
        foes while the sword of your enemies overtakes you, or else three days of
        the sword of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, pestilence on the land, with
        the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> destroying throughout all the
        territory of Israel.\u2019 Now decide what answer I shall return to him who
        sent me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to Gad, \u201CI am in great distress. Let me fall
        into the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for his mercy is very great,
        but do not let me fall into the hand of man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent a pestilence on Israel, and
        70,000 men of Israel fell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And God sent the angel to Jerusalem to destroy it, but as he was
        about to destroy it, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saw, and he relented
        from the calamity. And he said to the angel who was working destruction,
        \u201CIt is enough; now stay your hand.\u201D And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was standing by the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And David lifted his eyes and saw the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        standing between earth and heaven, and in his hand a drawn sword stretched
        out over Jerusalem. Then David and the elders, clothed in sackcloth, fell
        upon their faces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: David Builds an Altar'
      title: David Builds an Altar
      number: 17
      content: "And David said to God, \u201CWas it not I who gave command to number
        the people? It is I who have sinned and done great evil. But these sheep,
        what have they done? Please let your hand, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God, be against me and against my father\u2019s house. But do not let
        the plague be on your people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Gad
        to say to David that David should go up and raise an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So David went up at Gad\u2019s word, which he had spoken in the name
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now Ornan was threshing wheat. He turned and saw the angel, and his
        four sons who were with him hid themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'As David came to Ornan, Ornan looked and saw David and went out from
        the threshing floor and paid homage to David with his face to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And David said to Ornan, \u201CGive me the site of the threshing
        floor that I may build on it an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014give
        it to me at its full price\u2014that the plague may be averted from the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Ornan said to David, \u201CTake it, and let my lord the king
        do what seems good to him. See, I give the oxen for burnt offerings and the
        threshing sledges for the wood and the wheat for a grain offering; I give
        it all.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But King David said to Ornan, \u201CNo, but I will buy them for the
        full price. I will not take for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> what is yours,
        nor offer burnt offerings that cost me nothing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So David paid Ornan 600 shekels[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold by weight for
        the site. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:25 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And David built there an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and presented burnt offerings and peace offerings and called on the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]]  answered him with fire
        from heaven upon the altar of burnt offering. '
      comments:
      - number: '21:26 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded the angel, and he
        put his sword back into its sheath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'At that time, when David saw that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had answered him at the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite, he sacrificed
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For the tabernacle of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which Moses
        had made in the wilderness, and the altar of burnt offering were at that
        time in the high place at Gibeon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: but David could not go before it to inquire of God, for he was afraid
        of the sword of the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Prepares for Temple Building'
      title: David Prepares for Temple Building
      number: 1
      content: "  Then David said, \u201CHere shall be the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God and here the altar of burnt offering for Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'David commanded to gather together the resident aliens who were in
        the land of Israel, and he set stonecutters to prepare dressed stones for
        building the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'David also provided great quantities of iron for nails for the doors
        of the gates and for clamps, as well as bronze in quantities beyond weighing, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and cedar timbers without number, for the Sidonians and Tyrians brought
        great quantities of cedar to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Solomon Charged to Build the Temple'
      title: Solomon Charged to Build the Temple
      number: 5
      content: "For David said, \u201CSolomon my son is young and inexperienced,
        and the house that is to be built for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> must
        be exceedingly magnificent, of fame and glory throughout all lands. I will
        therefore make preparation for it.\u201D So David provided materials in great
        quantity before his death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he called for Solomon his son and charged him to build a house
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "David said to Solomon, \u201CMy son, I had it in my heart to build
        a house to the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me, saying,
        \u2018You have shed much blood and have waged great wars. You shall not build
        a house to my name, because you have shed so much blood before me on the
        earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Behold, a son shall be born to you who shall be a man of rest. I
        will give him rest from all his surrounding enemies. For his name shall be
        Solomon, and I will give peace and quiet to Israel in his days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He shall build a house for my name. He shall be my son, and I will
        be his father, and I will establish his royal throne in Israel forever.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNow, my son, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be with you, so
        that you may succeed in building the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, as he has spoken concerning you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Only, may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> grant you discretion and
        understanding, that when he gives you charge over Israel you may keep the
        law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then you will prosper if you are careful to observe the statutes
        and the rules that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded Moses for Israel.
        Be strong and courageous. Fear not; do not be dismayed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'With great pains I have provided for the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        100,000 talents[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, a million talents of silver, and bronze
        and iron beyond weighing, for there is so much of it; timber and stone, too,
        I have provided. To these you must add. '
      comments:
      - number: '22:14 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You have an abundance of workmen: stonecutters, masons, carpenters,
        and all kinds of craftsmen without number, skilled in working '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "gold, silver, bronze, and iron. Arise and work! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        be with you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'David also commanded all the leaders of Israel to help Solomon his
        son, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIs not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God with you? And
        has he not given you peace[[COMMENT(0)]] on every side? For he has delivered
        the inhabitants of the land into my hand, and the land is subdued before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and his people. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:18 '
        content: Or (see 22:9)
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now set your mind and heart to seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. Arise and build the sanctuary of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God, so that the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        the holy vessels of God may be brought into a house built for the name of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Organizes the Levites'
      title: David Organizes the Levites
      number: 1
      content: '    When David was old and full of days, he made Solomon his son
        king over Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'David[[COMMENT(0)]] assembled all the leaders of Israel and the priests
        and the Levites. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Levites, thirty years old and upward, were numbered, and the
        total was 38,000 men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTwenty-four thousand of these,\u201D David said,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        \u201Cshall have charge of the work in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        6,000 shall be officers and judges, "
      comments:
      - number: '23:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "4,000 gatekeepers, and 4,000 shall offer praises to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with the instruments that I have made for praise.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And David organized them in divisions corresponding to the sons of
        Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The sons of Gershon[[COMMENT(0)]] were Ladan and Shimei. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:7 '
        content: 'Vulgate (compare Septuagint, Syriac); Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Ladan: Jehiel the chief, and Zetham, and Joel, three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The sons of Shimei: Shelomoth, Haziel, and Haran, three. These were
        the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses of Ladan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the sons of Shimei: Jahath, Zina, and Jeush and Beriah. These
        four were the sons of Shimei. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Jahath was the chief, and Zizah the second; but Jeush and Beriah
        did not have many sons, therefore they became counted as a single father\u2019s
        house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, four. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The sons of Amram: Aaron and Moses. Aaron was set apart to dedicate
        the most holy things, that he and his sons forever should make offerings
        before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and minister to him and pronounce
        blessings in his name forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the sons of Moses the man of God were named among the tribe of
        Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Moses: Gershom and Eliezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Gershom: Shebuel the chief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Eliezer: Rehabiah the chief. Eliezer had no other sons,
        but the sons of Rehabiah were very many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The sons of Izhar: Shelomith the chief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Hebron: Jeriah the chief, Amariah the second, Jahaziel
        the third, and Jekameam the fourth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The sons of Uzziel: Micah the chief and Isshiah the second.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Mahli: Eleazar
        and Kish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Eleazar died having no sons, but only daughters; their kinsmen, the
        sons of Kish, married them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jeremoth, three.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  These were the sons of Levi by their fathers\u2019 houses, the
        heads of fathers\u2019 houses as they were listed according to the number
        of the names of the individuals from twenty years old and upward who were
        to do the work for the service of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For David said, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        Israel, has given rest to his people, and he dwells in Jerusalem forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And so the Levites no longer need to carry the tabernacle or any
        of the things for its service.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For by the last words of David the sons of Levi were numbered from
        twenty years old and upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For their duty was to assist the sons of Aaron for the service of
        the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, having the care of the courts
        and the chambers, the cleansing of all that is holy, and any work for the
        service of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Their duty was also to assist with the showbread, the flour for the
        grain offering, the wafers of unleavened bread, the baked offering, the offering
        mixed with oil, and all measures of quantity or size. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And they were to stand every morning, thanking and praising the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and likewise at evening, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and whenever burnt offerings were offered to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        on Sabbaths, new moons, and feast days, according to the number required
        of them, regularly before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Thus they were to keep charge of the tent of meeting and the sanctuary,
        and to attend the sons of Aaron, their brothers, for the service of the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Organizes the Priests'
      title: David Organizes the Priests
      number: 1
      content: '  The divisions of the sons of Aaron were these. The sons of Aaron:
        Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But Nadab and Abihu died before their father and had no children,
        so Eleazar and Ithamar became the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'With the help of Zadok of the sons of Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the
        sons of Ithamar, David organized them according to the appointed duties in
        their service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Since more chief men were found among the sons of Eleazar than among
        the sons of Ithamar, they organized them under sixteen heads of fathers\u2019
        houses of the sons of Eleazar, and eight of the sons of Ithamar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They divided them by lot, all alike, for there were sacred officers
        and officers of God among both the sons of Eleazar and the sons of Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the scribe Shemaiah, the son of Nethanel, a Levite, recorded
        them in the presence of the king and the princes and Zadok the priest and
        Ahimelech the son of Abiathar and the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses of
        the priests and of the Levites, one father\u2019s house being chosen for
        Eleazar and one chosen for Ithamar.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The first lot fell to Jehoiarib, the second to Jedaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the fifth to Malchijah, the sixth to Mijamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the seventh to Hakkoz, the eighth to Abijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the ninth to Jeshua, the tenth to Shecaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the eleventh to Eliashib, the twelfth to Jakim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the thirteenth to Huppah, the fourteenth to Jeshebeab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the fifteenth to Bilgah, the sixteenth to Immer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Happizzez, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the nineteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Jehezkel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the twenty-first to Jachin, the twenty-second to Gamul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the twenty-third to Delaiah, the twenty-fourth to Maaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These had as their appointed duty in their service to come into the
        house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> according to the procedure established
        for them by Aaron their father, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of
        Israel had commanded him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And of the rest of the sons of Levi: of the sons of Amram, Shubael;
        of the sons of Shubael, Jehdeiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Of Rehabiah: of the sons of Rehabiah, Isshiah the chief. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Of the Izharites, Shelomoth; of the sons of Shelomoth, Jahath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Hebron:[[COMMENT(0)]] Jeriah the chief, Amariah the second,
        Jahaziel the third, Jekameam the fourth. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:23 '
        content: 'Compare 23:19; Hebrew lacks Compare 23:19; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Uzziel, Micah; of the sons of Micah, Shamir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The brother of Micah, Isshiah; of the sons of Isshiah, Zechariah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Jaaziah: Beno.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:26 '
        content: Or ; also verse 27
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Merari: of Jaaziah, Beno, Shoham, Zaccur, and Ibri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Of Mahli: Eleazar, who had no sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Of Kish, the sons of Kish: Jerahmeel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The sons of Mushi: Mahli, Eder, and Jerimoth. These were the sons
        of the Levites according to their fathers\u2019 houses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "These also, the head of each father\u2019s house and his younger
        brother alike, cast lots, just as their brothers the sons of Aaron, in the
        presence of King David, Zadok, Ahimelech, and the heads of fathers\u2019
        houses of the priests and of the Levites."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Organizes the Musicians'
      title: David Organizes the Musicians
      number: 1
      content: '  David and the chiefs of the service also set apart for the service
        the sons of Asaph, and of Heman, and of Jeduthun, who prophesied with lyres,
        with harps, and with cymbals. The list of those who did the work and of their
        duties was: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Of the sons of Asaph: Zaccur, Joseph, Nethaniah, and Asharelah, sons
        of Asaph, under the direction of Asaph, who prophesied under the direction
        of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Of Jeduthun, the sons of Jeduthun: Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Shimei,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the direction of their father Jeduthun,
        who prophesied with the lyre in thanksgiving and praise to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments:
      - number: '25:3 '
        content: 'One Hebrew manuscript, Septuagint; most Hebrew manuscripts lack '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Of Heman, the sons of Heman: Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel
        and Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, and Romamti-ezer, Joshbekashah,
        Mallothi, Hothir, Mahazioth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "All these were the sons of Heman the king\u2019s seer, according
        to the promise of God to exalt him, for God had given Heman fourteen sons
        and three daughters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They were all under the direction of their father in the music in
        the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with cymbals, harps, and lyres
        for the service of the house of God. Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman were under
        the order of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The number of them along with their brothers, who were trained in
        singing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all who were skillful, was 288. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they cast lots for their duties, small and great, teacher and
        pupil alike.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The first lot fell for Asaph to Joseph; the second to Gedaliah, to
        him and his brothers and his sons, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the third to Zaccur, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the fourth to Izri, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the fifth to Nethaniah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the sixth to Bukkiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the seventh to Jesharelah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the eighth to Jeshaiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the ninth to Mattaniah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the tenth to Shimei, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the eleventh to Azarel, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the twelfth to Hashabiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'to the thirteenth, Shubael, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'to the fourteenth, Mattithiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'to the fifteenth, to Jeremoth, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'to the sixteenth, to Hananiah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'to the seventeenth, to Joshbekashah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'to the eighteenth, to Hanani, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'to the nineteenth, to Mallothi, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'to the twentieth, to Eliathah, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'to the twenty-first, to Hothir, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'to the twenty-second, to Giddalti, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'to the twenty-third, to Mahazioth, his sons and his brothers, twelve; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: to the twenty-fourth, to Romamti-ezer, his sons and his brothers,
        twelve.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Divisions of the Gatekeepers'
      title: Divisions of the Gatekeepers
      number: 1
      content: '  As for the divisions of the gatekeepers: of the Korahites, Meshelemiah
        the son of Kore, of the sons of Asaph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Meshelemiah had sons: Zechariah the firstborn, Jediael the second,
        Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Elam the fifth, Jehohanan the sixth, Eliehoenai the seventh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Obed-edom had sons: Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second,
        Joah the third, Sachar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, Peullethai the eighth, for
        God blessed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Also to his son Shemaiah were sons born who were rulers in their
        fathers\u2019 houses, for they were men of great ability. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Shemaiah: Othni, Rephael, Obed and Elzabad, whose brothers
        were able men, Elihu and Semachiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All these were of the sons of Obed-edom with their sons and brothers,
        able men qualified for the service; sixty-two of Obed-edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Meshelemiah had sons and brothers, able men, eighteen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Hosah, of the sons of Merari, had sons: Shimri the chief (for
        though he was not the firstborn, his father made him chief), '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the third, Zechariah the fourth: all
        the sons and brothers of Hosah were thirteen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'These divisions of the gatekeepers, corresponding to their chief
        men, had duties, just as their brothers did, ministering in the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And they cast lots by fathers\u2019 houses, small and great alike,
        for their gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The lot for the east fell to Shelemiah. They cast lots also for his
        son Zechariah, a shrewd counselor, and his lot came out for the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Obed-edom\u2019s came out for the south, and to his sons was allotted
        the gatehouse. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For Shuppim and Hosah it came out for the west, at the gate of Shallecheth
        on the road that goes up. Watch corresponded to watch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'On the east there were six each day,[[COMMENT(0)]] on the north four
        each day, on the south four each day, as well as two and two at the gatehouse. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:17 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And for the colonnade[[COMMENT(0)]] on the west there were four at
        the road and two at the colonnade. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:18 '
        content: Or ; Hebrew (meaning unknown); twice in this verse
    - name: '19: Treasurers and Other Officials'
      title: Treasurers and Other Officials
      number: 19
      content: 'These were the divisions of the gatekeepers among the Korahites and
        the sons of Merari.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And of the Levites, Ahijah had charge of the treasuries of the house
        of God and the treasuries of the dedicated gifts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The sons of Ladan, the sons of the Gershonites belonging to Ladan,
        the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses belonging to Ladan the Gershonite:
        Jehieli.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:21 '
        content: The Hebrew of verse 21 is uncertain
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The sons of Jehieli, Zetham, and Joel his brother, were in charge
        of the treasuries of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Of the Amramites, the Izharites, the Hebronites, and the Uzzielites\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and Shebuel the son of Gershom, son of Moses, was chief officer in
        charge of the treasuries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'His brothers: from Eliezer were his son Rehabiah, and his son Jeshaiah,
        and his son Joram, and his son Zichri, and his son Shelomoth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "This Shelomoth and his brothers were in charge of all the treasuries
        of the dedicated gifts that David the king and the heads of the fathers\u2019
        houses and the officers of the thousands and the hundreds and the commanders
        of the army had dedicated. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'From spoil won in battles they dedicated gifts for the maintenance
        of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Also all that Samuel the seer and Saul the son of Kish and Abner
        the son of Ner and Joab the son of Zeruiah had dedicated\u2014all dedicated
        gifts were in the care of Shelomoth[[COMMENT(0)]] and his brothers.  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:28 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Of the Izharites, Chenaniah and his sons were appointed to external
        duties for Israel, as officers and judges. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Of the Hebronites, Hashabiah and his brothers, 1,700 men of ability,
        had the oversight of Israel westward of the Jordan for all the work of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and for the service of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Of the Hebronites, Jerijah was chief of the Hebronites of whatever
        genealogy or fathers\u2019 houses. (In the fortieth year of David\u2019s
        reign search was made and men of great ability among them were found at Jazer
        in Gilead.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "King David appointed him and his brothers, 2,700 men of ability,
        heads of fathers\u2019 houses, to have the oversight of the Reubenites, the
        Gadites and the half-tribe of the Manassites for everything pertaining to
        God and for the affairs of the king."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Military Divisions'
      title: Military Divisions
      number: 1
      content: "  This is the number of the people of Israel, the heads of fathers\u2019
        houses, the commanders of thousands and hundreds, and their officers who
        served the king in all matters concerning the divisions that came and went,
        month after month throughout the year, each division numbering 24,000:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Jashobeam the son of Zabdiel was in charge of the first division
        in the first month; in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He was a descendant of Perez and was chief of all the commanders.
        He served for the first month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Dodai the Ahohite[[COMMENT(0)]] was in charge of the division of
        the second month; in his division were 24,000. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:4 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The third commander, for the third month, was Benaiah, the son of
        Jehoiada the chief priest; in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'This is the Benaiah who was a mighty man of the thirty and in command
        of the thirty; Ammizabad his son was in charge of his division.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:6 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Asahel the brother of Joab was fourth, for the fourth month, and
        his son Zebadiah after him; in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The fifth commander, for the fifth month, was Shamhuth the Izrahite;
        in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Sixth, for the sixth month, was Ira, the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite;
        in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Seventh, for the seventh month, was Helez the Pelonite, of the sons
        of Ephraim; in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Eighth, for the eighth month, was Sibbecai the Hushathite, of the
        Zerahites; in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Ninth, for the ninth month, was Abiezer of Anathoth, a Benjaminite;
        in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Tenth, for the tenth month, was Maharai of Netophah, of the Zerahites;
        in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Eleventh, for the eleventh month, was Benaiah of Pirathon, of the
        sons of Ephraim; in his division were 24,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Leaders of Tribes'
      title: Leaders of Tribes
      number: 15
      content: 'Twelfth, for the twelfth month, was Heldai the Netophathite, of Othniel;
        in his division were 24,000.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Over the tribes of Israel, for the Reubenites, Eliezer the son of
        Zichri was chief officer; for the Simeonites, Shephatiah the son of Maacah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for Levi, Hashabiah the son of Kemuel; for Aaron, Zadok; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "for Judah, Elihu, one of David\u2019s brothers; for Issachar, Omri
        the son of Michael; "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'for Zebulun, Ishmaiah the son of Obadiah; for Naphtali, Jeremoth
        the son of Azriel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'for the Ephraimites, Hoshea the son of Azaziah; for the half-tribe
        of Manasseh, Joel the son of Pedaiah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'for the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead, Iddo the son of Zechariah;
        for Benjamin, Jaasiel the son of Abner; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'for Dan, Azarel the son of Jeroham. These were the leaders of the
        tribes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'David did not count those below twenty years of age, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had promised to make Israel as many as the stars of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Joab the son of Zeruiah began to count, but did not finish. Yet wrath
        came upon Israel for this, and the number was not entered in the chronicles
        of King David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Over the king\u2019s treasuries was Azmaveth the son of Adiel; and
        over the treasuries in the country, in the cities, in the villages, and in
        the towers, was Jonathan the son of Uzziah; "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and over those who did the work of the field for tilling the soil
        was Ezri the son of Chelub; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and over the vineyards was Shimei the Ramathite; and over the produce
        of the vineyards for the wine cellars was Zabdi the Shiphmite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Over the olive and sycamore trees in the Shephelah was Baal-hanan
        the Gederite; and over the stores of oil was Joash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Over the herds that pastured in Sharon was Shitrai the Sharonite;
        over the herds in the valleys was Shaphat the son of Adlai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Over the camels was Obil the Ishmaelite; and over the donkeys was
        Jehdeiah the Meronothite. Over the flocks was Jaziz the Hagrite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "All these were stewards of King David\u2019s property.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Jonathan, David\u2019s uncle, was a counselor, being a man of understanding
        and a scribe. He and Jehiel the son of Hachmoni attended the king\u2019s
        sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Ahithophel was the king\u2019s counselor, and Hushai the Archite
        was the king\u2019s friend. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Ahithophel was succeeded by Jehoiada the son of Benaiah, and Abiathar.
        Joab was commander of the king\u2019s army."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Charge to Israel"
      title: "David\u2019s Charge to Israel"
      number: 1
      content: '    David assembled at Jerusalem all the officials of Israel, the
        officials of the tribes, the officers of the divisions that served the king,
        the commanders of thousands, the commanders of hundreds, the stewards of
        all the property and livestock of the king and his sons, together with the
        palace officials, the mighty men and all the seasoned warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then King David rose to his feet and said: \u201CHear me, my brothers
        and my people. I had it in my heart to build a house of rest for the ark
        of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and for the footstool
        of our God, and I made preparations for building. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But God said to me, \u2018You may not build a house for my name,
        for you are a man of war and have shed blood.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Israel chose me from all
        my father\u2019s house to be king over Israel forever. For he chose Judah
        as leader, and in the house of Judah my father\u2019s house, and among my
        father\u2019s sons he took pleasure in me to make me king over all Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And of all my sons (for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given
        me many sons) he has chosen Solomon my son to sit on the throne of the kingdom
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to me, \u2018It is Solomon your son who shall build my house
        and my courts, for I have chosen him to be my son, and I will be his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I will establish his kingdom forever if he continues strong in keeping
        my commandments and my rules, as he is today.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "8: David\u2019s Charge to Solomon"
      title: "David\u2019s Charge to Solomon"
      number: 8
      content: 'Now therefore in the sight of all Israel, the assembly of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and in the hearing of our God, observe and seek out all the commandments
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, that you may possess this good
        land and leave it for an inheritance to your children after you forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd you, Solomon my son, know the God of your father and serve
        him with a whole heart and with a willing mind, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        searches all hearts and understands every plan and thought. If you seek him,
        he will be found by you, but if you forsake him, he will cast you off forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Be careful now, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen you
        to build a house for the sanctuary; be strong and do it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then David gave Solomon his son the plan of the vestibule of the
        temple,[[COMMENT(0)]] and of its houses, its treasuries, its upper rooms,
        and its inner chambers, and of the room for the mercy seat; '
      comments:
      - number: '28:11 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and the plan of all that he had in mind for the courts of the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all the surrounding chambers, the treasuries
        of the house of God, and the treasuries for dedicated gifts; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for the divisions of the priests and of the Levites, and all the
        work of the service in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; for
        all the vessels for the service in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the weight of gold for all golden vessels for each service, the weight
        of silver vessels for each service, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the weight of the golden lampstands and their lamps, the weight of
        gold for each lampstand and its lamps, the weight of silver for a lampstand
        and its lamps, according to the use of each lampstand in the service, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the weight of gold for each table for the showbread, the silver for
        the silver tables, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and pure gold for the forks, the basins and the cups; for the golden
        bowls and the weight of each; for the silver bowls and the weight of each; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'for the altar of incense made of refined gold, and its weight; also
        his plan for the golden chariot of the cherubim that spread their wings and
        covered the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAll this he made clear to me in writing from the hand of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all the work to be done according to the plan.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then David said to Solomon his son, \u201CBe strong and courageous
        and do it. Do not be afraid and do not be dismayed, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God, even my God, is with you. He will not leave you or forsake you, until
        all the work for the service of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is finished. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And behold the divisions of the priests and the Levites for all the
        service of the house of God; and with you in all the work will be every willing
        man who has skill for any kind of service; also the officers and all the
        people will be wholly at your command.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Offerings for the Temple'
      title: Offerings for the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "  And David the king said to all the assembly, \u201CSolomon my son,
        whom alone God has chosen, is young and inexperienced, and the work is great,
        for the palace will not be for man but for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I have provided for the house of my God, so far as I was able,
        the gold for the things of gold, the silver for the things of silver, and
        the bronze for the things of bronze, the iron for the things of iron, and
        wood for the things of wood, besides great quantities of onyx and stones
        for setting, antimony, colored stones, all sorts of precious stones and marble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Moreover, in addition to all that I have provided for the holy house,
        I have a treasure of my own of gold and silver, and because of my devotion
        to the house of my God I give it to the house of my God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '3,000 talents[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, of the gold of Ophir, and 7,000
        talents of refined silver, for overlaying the walls of the house,  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:4 '
        content: 'A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilogramsSeptuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and for all the work to be done by craftsmen, gold for the things
        of gold and silver for the things of silver. Who then will offer willingly,
        consecrating himself[[COMMENT(0)]] today to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:5 '
        content: 'Or ; Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the leaders of fathers\u2019 houses made their freewill offerings,
        as did also the leaders of the tribes, the commanders of thousands and of
        hundreds, and the officers over the king\u2019s work. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They gave for the service of the house of God 5,000 talents and 10,000
        darics[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, 10,000 talents of silver, 18,000 talents of
        bronze and 100,000 talents of iron. '
      comments:
      - number: '29:7 '
        content: A was a coin weighing about 1/4 ounce or 8.5 grams
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And whoever had precious stones gave them to the treasury of the
        house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, in the care of Jehiel the Gershonite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: David Prays in the Assembly'
      title: David Prays in the Assembly
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the people rejoiced because they had given willingly, for with
        a whole heart they had offered freely to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        David the king also rejoiced greatly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore David blessed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in the presence
        of all the assembly. And David said: \u201CBlessed are you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel our father, forever and ever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yours, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, is the greatness and the power
        and the glory and the victory and the majesty, for all that is in the heavens
        and in the earth is yours. Yours is the kingdom, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and you are exalted as head above all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Both riches and honor come from you, and you rule over all. In your
        hand are power and might, and in your hand it is to make great and to give
        strength to all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And now we thank you, our God, and praise your glorious name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBut who am I, and what is my people, that we should be able
        thus to offer willingly? For all things come from you, and of your own have
        we given you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For we are strangers before you and sojourners, as all our fathers
        were. Our days on the earth are like a shadow, and there is no abiding.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:15 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew , or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, all this abundance that we
        have provided for building you a house for your holy name comes from your
        hand and is all your own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I know, my God, that you test the heart and have pleasure in uprightness.
        In the uprightness of my heart I have freely offered all these things, and
        now I have seen your people, who are present here, offering freely and joyously
        to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel,
        our fathers, keep forever such purposes and thoughts in the hearts of your
        people, and direct their hearts toward you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Grant to Solomon my son a whole heart that he may keep your commandments,
        your testimonies, and your statutes, performing all, and that he may build
        the palace for which I have made provision.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then David said to all the assembly, \u201CBless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.\u201D And all the assembly blessed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of their fathers, and bowed their heads and paid homage to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and to the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they offered sacrifices to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and
        on the next day offered burnt offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        1,000 bulls, 1,000 rams, and 1,000 lambs, with their drink offerings, and
        sacrifices in abundance for all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Solomon Anointed King'
      title: Solomon Anointed King
      number: 22
      content: 'And they ate and drank before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on
        that day with great gladness.And they made Solomon the son of David king
        the second time, and they anointed him as prince for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and Zadok as priest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Then Solomon sat on the throne of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        as king in place of David his father. And he prospered, and all Israel obeyed
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'All the leaders and the mighty men, and also all the sons of King
        David, pledged their allegiance to King Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: The Death of David'
      title: The Death of David
      number: 25
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made Solomon very great in the
        sight of all Israel and bestowed on him such royal majesty as had not been
        on any king before him in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Thus David the son of Jesse reigned over all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The time that he reigned over Israel was forty years. He reigned
        seven years in Hebron and thirty-three years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then he died at a good age, full of days, riches, and honor. And
        Solomon his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now the acts of King David, from first to last, are written in the
        Chronicles of Samuel the seer, and in the Chronicles of Nathan the prophet,
        and in the Chronicles of Gad the seer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: with accounts of all his rule and his might and of the circumstances
        that came upon him and upon Israel and upon all the kingdoms of the countries.
      comments: []
